<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Short Description</b><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">This defines the interval after which an application with
inactive connections from connection pool will be closed. This setting will
affect applications using the HTTPS communication APIs.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Long Description</b><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class="MsoNormal">In OM scenario , opcmsga is an HTTP client which makes
Connections from the node to the BBC communication broker. If the connections
from an Http Client like opcmsga is inactive for more than a minute closing the
connection would improve the performance. Hence from OA version 11.02 and above
AUTO_CONNECTION_CLOSE_INTERVAL=60, for opcmsga.</p><h2 style="margin: 0.25in 0in 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="mso-ansi-font-size:
13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:
191;font-weight:normal">CHROOT_PATH&nbsp;</span></span></h2><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
