  </td>
  <td width="504" valign="top" style="width: 5.25in; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: black; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: black; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;
  mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#010101">&nbsp;</span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><b style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">Short Description</b><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">The BBC Communications Broker(BBC CB) is the central point
of entry to a node for all applications on the node using the BBC API library,
for higher security the BBC CB may be chrootd on startup for UNIX systems.
Chroot restricts the part of the file system visible to the CB process thus
reducing exposure to hackers. So this variable provides a way to protect the
Communication Broker port.<span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Long Description</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">This variable value specifies chroot path for the ovbbccb
process to use. This is effective only on UNIX/Linux nodes. During BBC CB
process start-up chroot operation is performed to the value set in this
variable if its present else default path &lt;OvDataDir&gt; is used. As a
result, the file system above the &lt;OvDataDir&gt; directory or the path
specified in this config variable becomes invisible to the ovbbccb process. So
this means that all files under /etc become inaccessible, for eg: files like
/etc/hosts, /etc/resolv.conf and /etc/nsswitch.conf can't be accessed. This
also mean that other BBC CB parameters such as SERVER_BIND_ADDR must therefore
use IP addresses instead of hostnames when the CHROOT_PATH parameter is active
(default on UNIX platforms).</p><h2 style="margin: 0.25in 0in 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><a name="_Toc491176826"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="mso-ansi-font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;
mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;
mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;
mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;
mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;
color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:191;font-weight:normal">DISABLE_REL_PATH</span></span></a><span class="LabelChar"><span style="mso-ansi-font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;
mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;
mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;
mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;
mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;
color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:191"><o:p></o:p></span></span></h2><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
 <tbody><tr>
