  &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Related variables<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width="504" valign="top" style="width: 5.25in; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-bottom-color: black; border-right-width: 1pt; border-right-color: black; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:
  normal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,sans-serif">IPCACHE_DISABLED</span><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:
  &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
  color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:191"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;"><b>Short Description</b></span><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">HOSTNAME_CACHE_TIMEOUT improves the performance when the
hostname is resolved with DNS.&nbsp; Hostnames
are cached. However if DHCP is changing the&nbsp;
IP very frequently then we should make HOSTNAME_CACHE_TIMEOUT very small.</p><p class="MsoNormal">Once a hostname is resolved using getaddrinfo ,&nbsp; until cache timeout (default 30 minutes ) has
expired , every subsequent attempts of same node name is retrieved from the
resolvable IP Cache rather than doing a getaddrinfo() again. This ensures that
DNS latency related delay in message processing is eliminated thus improving
the performance of the subagent. Suppose there are 2000 nodes monitored by OM
that intercepts huge amount of messages/events periodically, now if these
events contain hostnames that are to be resolved, specifying
HOSTNAME_CACHE_TIMEOUT eliminates repeated resolutions and thereby improving
performance. Each subagent maintains its own hostname cache.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Long Description</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Specifies the number of seconds before a hostname cache
entry will be reset. BBC caches the hostname lookup. After the specified number
of seconds, the cache entry will be deleted. The default<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;is 1800 seconds or 30
minutes. Maximum is 1 year, minimum is 0. If set to zero the cache will be
disabled.<span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal">The cache timeout can be increased via this variable eg: 24
hours<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">[xpl.net]<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">HOSTNAME_CACHE_TIMEOUT=86400<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">HOSTNAME_CACHE_TIMEOUT is valid only when IPCACHE_DISABLED
is false.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_Toc491176831"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);">KEEP_CONNECTIONS_OPEN</span></span></a><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
