</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span><span style="color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;"><font size="3">Short
Description</font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;">SNF API
provides </span></span><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%;">the Store</span></span><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"> and Forward mechanism for the&nbsp; guaranteed delivery of an event and
messages.The snf related messages are stored in the buffered file at
%ovdatadir%/tmp/OpC/mgmt_sv/snf<o:p></o:p></span></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">KEEP_CONNECTIONS_OPEN
is one of the settings recommended for performance improvements for snf
functionality. This setting minimize the need to establish new SSL connections
(which is where the memory growth occurs). KEEP_CONNECTIONS_OPEN will instruct
BBC SnF to keep connections open even if not currently used.</font></span></span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><b>Long
Description</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">Snf is used
for guaranteed delivery of messages in MOM or backup server functionalities
that OM Server offers. <o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal">

















</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">The
variable KEEP_CONNECTIONS_OPEN Specifies, if the connection shall be closed
after a queue got completely processed. If set to true it says open and has to
be closed by the application by calling SnfClient::CloseUnusedConnections().</font></span></span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><h2><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size: 13pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);">REQUEST_TIMEOUT</span></span><span class="LabelChar"><span style="font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-ascii-font-family:
&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:
191"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p></h2><table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
 <tbody><tr>
  <td width="230" valign="top" style="width: 172.25pt; border-width: 1pt; border-left-style: solid; border-color: black; border-image: initial; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
