</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;"><b>Short
Description</b></span><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">These
settings are used to tune the Socket incoming connections and it is very rarely
changed.&nbsp;</font></span></span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">When the
number of nodes to be monitored are high , we might reduce the</span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">REQUEST_TIMEOUT to a lower value on the Http
Server. When the nodes are sluggish to respond, the</span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">REQUEST_TIMEOUT might have to be increased.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><b>Long
Description</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">REQUEST_TIMEOUT
for [bbc.cb] specifies the number of seconds the ovbbccb server waits for&nbsp; data on an incoming request. If data is not
received&nbsp; within the specified number of
seconds, the request is requeued.&nbsp; The
default value is 1s.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></span></span><span class="LabelChar" style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">In case of
a generic Bbc Http Server , REQUEST_TIMEOUT specifies the number of seconds the
HTTP server waits for an incoming request on an open connection. After this
time the application&nbsp;</font></span></span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent; color: windowtext;">gets an InterruptedIOException_t.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">For
[bbc.http] namespace, default value is 300s</font><span style="font-size: 13pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></span></span></p><h2 style="margin: 0.25in 0in 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><a name="_Toc491176833"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="mso-ansi-font-size:13.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
