</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><b><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">Short Description</span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Specifies the number of seconds the HTTP client waits for an
incoming response.&nbsp;<span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">default value</span><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">for
RESPONSE_TIMEOUT is</span><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">300</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>Long Description</b><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">













</p><p class="MsoNormal">These settings are used to tune the Socket outgoing
connections and it is very rarely changed.When the number of nodes to be
monitored are high, we might reduce the RESPONSE_TIMEOUT to a lower value on
the Http Server. When the nodes are sluggish to respond, the&nbsp; RESPONSE_TIMEOUT might have to be increased.<span style="color: rgb(46, 116, 181); font-size: 13pt; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:
&quot;Gadugi&quot;,sans-serif"><u><b>Background</b>:</u><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal">

</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;"><font size="3">A TCP/IP connection is identified by a four element tuple:
{source IP, source port, destination IP, destination port}.</font><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;"><font size="3">To establish a TCP/IP connection only a destination IP and
port number are needed, the operating system automatically selects source IP
and port. But few customers would want an option configured source IP and port
to some specific address and port of their choice. When a connection is made
the operating system would to select an unused source port number and by
default localhost would be selected as IP.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;"><font size="3">Applications using BBC API for HTTP communication, have an
option to configure the source IP and port through below configuration
variables:<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-add-space:
auto;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:107%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"></p><ul><li><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Wingdings;">n<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">SERVER_BIND_ADDR
</span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">[ apply/specific to HTTP
Server ]</span></li><li><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Wingdings;">n<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">SERVER_PORT
</span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">[ apply/specific to HTTP
Server ]</span></li><li><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Wingdings;">n<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">CLIENT_BIND_ADDR
</span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">[ apply/specific to HTTP Client
]</span></li><li><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Wingdings;">n<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; line-height: 107%; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">CLIENT_PORT
</span><span style="font-size: medium; letter-spacing: 0.2px; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: transparent; font-family: Gadugi, sans-serif;">[ apply/specific to HTTP Client
]</span></li></ul><p></p><h2 style="margin: 0.25in 0in 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="mso-ansi-font-size:
13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;
mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:
191;font-weight:normal">SERVER_PORT</span></span><span class="LabelChar"><span style="mso-ansi-font-size:13.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;
mso-ascii-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:major-latin;
mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;
mso-hansi-font-family:&quot;Calibri Light&quot;;mso-hansi-theme-font:major-latin;
mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi;
color:#2E74B5;mso-themecolor:accent1;mso-themeshade:191"><o:p></o:p></span></span></h2><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="margin-bottom:8.0pt;mso-add-space:
auto;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:107%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--></p><div>

<table class="MsoTableGrid" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="0" style="border-left: none;">
 <tbody><tr>
  <td width="230" valign="top" style="width: 172.25pt; border-width: 1pt; border-left-style: solid; border-color: black; border-image: initial; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
  <p class="Label"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Gadugi&quot;,sans-serif"><b>Type</b></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Gadugi&quot;,sans-serif;color:black"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width="504" valign="top" style="width: 5.25in; border-top-width: 1pt; border-right-width: 1pt; border-bottom-width: 1pt; border-top-color: black; border-right-color: black; border-bottom-color: black; border-image: initial; border-left: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt;">
