 </tr>
</tbody></table><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: rgb(46, 116, 181);"><o:p style="">&nbsp;</o:p></span></span><span style="color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;"><b>Short Description</b></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">This variable is used to
define/configure client bind address value for an HTTP communication done using
BBC API.<o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><b>Long Description</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">Bind address for the client
requests. When the default INADDR_ANY is used as the address when calling
bind() , the socket accepts connections to all the IPs of the machine. We can
also assign hostname or IP. When we have proxy setup we might need
CLIENT_BIND_ADDR.</font></span></span><span style="font-size: medium; color: windowtext; letter-spacing: 0.2px; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="MsoNormal">















</p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3">For example, consider an OA
setup which is multi-homed. This means the system can have multiple IP addresses.
If the interface to communicate outside has to be explicitly specified,
CLIENT_BIND_ADDRESS is the configuration to use. Let us suppose the system has
3 IPs.&nbsp; Ovcert request is a client
application to send a certificate request. If the user wants to explicitly set
the bind address to a specific IP out of the 3 IPs of the system,
CLIENT_BIND_ADDRESS can be configured with this specific IP. This would make
sure that the ovcert request would use the specified IP for its outward
communication.</font><span style="font-size: 13pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span class="LabelChar"><span style="line-height: 107%; color: windowtext;"><font size="3"><br></font></span></span></p></div><p class="MsoNormal">









</p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>